<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD0FF93FC9FC51247AAFABC" blockId="2.[831,1437,848,1386]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">
FSL.EM.1788: D: 53.0 (100) – Wh: 30.0 (57) – Wb: 16.0 (30) – U: 5.0 (9) – v: 2.4 (5) – Wb/Wh: 0.53 FSL.EM.1788: D: 70.0 (100) –Wh: 38.0 (54) – Wb: 21.0 (30) – U: 6.5 (9) – v: 3.7 (5) – Wb/Wh: 0.55 
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD0FF93FC9FC59241F5FADC" bold="true" box="[831,963,1265,1289]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Description</emphasis>
: A single specimen preserved as calcareous internal mould of a subadult phragmocone, 
<quantity id="FA51E381FFD0FF93FA8DC472474AFAFC" box="[1325,1404,1297,1321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="70.0">70 mm</quantity>
in diameter, with an estimated total diameter of at least 
<quantity id="FA51E381FFD0FF93FC9FC43141ADFABC" box="[831,923,1362,1386]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="140.0">140 mm</quantity>
. The discoidal shell shows involute coiling with
</paragraph>
<caption id="69D61EECFFD0FF93FF37C68640F4F7CD" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" startId="2.[151,186,2021,2043]" targetBox="[151,1427,1451,1984]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD0FF93FF37C68640F4F7CD" blockId="2.[151,1436,2021,2072]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 1: The holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD0FF93FE26C685413DF82E" authority="H. DOUVILLE, 1916" authorityName="H. DOUVILLE" authorityYear="1916" box="[390,779,2021,2044]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD0FF93FE26C6854075F82F" box="[390,579,2021,2043]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="160">Knemiceras gracile</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD0FF93FDC8C685413DF82E" author="DOUVILLE" box="[616,779,2021,2044]" pageId="2" pageNumber="160" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref8116" refString="DOUVILLE, H. (1916) - Les terrains secondaires dans le Massif du Moghara, a l'E de l'isthme de Suez. Memoires de l'Academie des Sciences de Paris (2), 54: 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1916">DOUVILLÉ, 1916</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, FSL.EM.1788, NW of Talat el Fellahin (now Gabal Maaza), SE of Gabal Maghara, north Sinai, Egypt, Early Albian.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FE57C04B4014FEEE" blockId="3.[503,546,296,315]" box="[503,546,296,315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FE57C04B4014FEEE" bold="true" box="[503,546,296,315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<quantity id="FA51E381FFD1FF92FE57C04B4014FEEE" box="[503,546,296,315]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<caption id="69D61EECFFD1FF92FF37C0904315FDA9" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" startId="3.[151,186,499,521]" targetBox="[210,671,306,442]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FF37C0904315FDA9" blockId="3.[151,756,499,636]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
Fig. 2: Suture of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FD88C0974398FDF3" authority="H. DOUVILLE, 1916" authorityName="H. DOUVILLE" authorityYear="1916" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FD88C09740C2FDDD" box="[552,756,499,521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras gracile</emphasis>
H. 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FEA7C3734398FDF3" author="DOUVILLE" box="[263,430,528,551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref8116" refString="DOUVILLE, H. (1916) - Les terrains secondaires dans le Massif du Moghara, a l'E de l'isthme de Suez. Memoires de l'Academie des Sciences de Paris (2), 54: 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1916">DOUVILLÉ, 1916</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, FSL.EM.1788, NW of Talat el Fellahin (now Gabal Maaza), SE of Gabal Maghara, north Sinai, Egypt, Early Albian (After DOUVILLÉ, 1926).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FF37C3DB4058FA83" blockId="3.[151,757,696,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
a very narrow umbilicus, comprising 9% of the diameter. The umbilicus increases in diameter on the last stages of ontogenesis, as suggested by traces on the flanks of the last whorl of the phragmocone. The umbilical wall is shallow and vertical with sharp umbilical shoulder. The whorl section is compressed, subtriangular (Wb/ Wh between 0.53 and 0.55), with maximum width at about the inner third of the flanks. The flanks are gently convex, converging to a very narrow venter (ventral thickness comprising less than 5% of the diameter). The ventral area is grooved and smooth, limited by rows of weak ventrolateral bullae, forming sharp, crenulated ventrolateral edges. The lateral ornament is almost nonexistent and restricted to weak, broad, coarse, regularly alternating primary and intercalatory ribs, up to a diameter of 
<quantity id="FA51E381FFD1FF92FE86C5FF43A1FB61" box="[294,407,1180,1204]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" unit="mm" value="45.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="40.0">40-50 mm</quantity>
. The ribbing style, while not well expressed, is characteristic of the genus. Beyond 
<quantity id="FA51E381FFD1FF92FD09C5DE40C5FB01" box="[681,755,1213,1237]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
in diameter, the lateral ribbing becomes inconspicuous, and tends to disappear altogether. The body chamber is unknown from the 
<typeStatus id="E212F0C6FFD1FF92FED4C47D43E3FAE3" box="[372,469,1310,1334]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">holotype</typeStatus>
. The suture shows entire saddles and feebly indentated lobes (
<figureCitation id="A59252E1FFD1FF92FDBFC45D4057FA83" box="[543,609,1342,1366]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[151,186,499,521]" captionTargetBox="[210,671,306,442]" captionTargetId="graphics-631@3.[210,671,306,442]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2: Suture of the holotype of Knemiceras gracile H. DOUVILLÉ, 1916, FSL.EM.1788, NW of Talat el Fellahin (now Gabal Maaza), SE of Gabal Maghara, north Sinai, Egypt, Early Albian (After DOUVILLÉ, 1926)." pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="69D61EECFFD1FF92FC9FC565469BFBA6" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" startId="3.[831,866,1030,1052]" targetBox="[836,1436,257,978]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FC9FC565469BFBA6" blockId="3.[831,1437,1030,1139]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
Fig. 3: 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FC2DC5644613FBC9" box="[909,1061,1031,1052]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FC2DC5644636FBC9" box="[909,1024,1031,1052]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
ind., the specimen figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FAFDC56441F1FBED" author="BASSE" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="411 - 472" refId="ref7350" refString="BASSE, E. (1940) - Les Cephalopodes des massifs cotiers syriens. Notes et Memoires du Haut-Commissariat de la Republique Francaise en Syrie et au Liban, 3: Etudes paleontologiques, 411 - 472." type="book chapter" year="1940">BASSE (1940</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 4, fig. 1; text fig. 9, 10), as 
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FA8AC54741E1FB80" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FA8AC54741E5FB80" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracile">Knemiceras gracile</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from unknown stratigraphical level of the Albian of Mdereidj, Lebanon.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="75B31DEFFFD1FF92FF37C43D4192F8EF" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FF37C43D437BF9CD" blockId="3.[151,757,696,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FF37C43D432EFAA3" bold="true" box="[151,280,1374,1398]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Discussion:</emphasis>
This species remains poorly known, but seems to represent a primitive morphology of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FF37C4C34385FA62" authority="BOHM, 1898" authorityName="BOHM" authorityYear="1898" box="[151,435,1439,1464]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FF37C4C34320FA62" box="[151,278,1440,1463]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FE84C4C34385FA62" author="BOHM" box="[292,435,1439,1464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="183 - 208" refId="ref7467" refString="BOHM, J. (1898) - Uber Ammonites pedernalis Von Buch. Zeitschrift der Deutschen Geologischen Gesellschaft, 50: 183 - 208." type="journal article" year="1898">BÖHM, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, characterized by an almost lack of lateral ornament, a very narrowly grooved ventral area, and a suture with entire saddles and feebly indentated lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FF37C74343D5F8CE" blockId="3.[151,757,696,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
The 
<typeStatus id="E212F0C6FFD1FF92FF6DC743431CF9ED" box="[205,298,1568,1592]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">holotype</typeStatus>
seems to co-occur with an unequivocal juvenile representative of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FD92C7224347F9AC" authority="de GROSSOUVRE, 1894" authorityName="de GROSSOUVRE" authorityYear="1894" class="Cephalopoda" family="Douvilleiceratidae" genus="Douvilleiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FD92C72240F9F98C" box="[562,719,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Douvilleiceras</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FF37C7024347F9AC" author="GROSSOUVRE" box="[151,369,1633,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" refId="ref8332" refString="GROSSOUVRE, A. de (1894) - Recherches sur la Craie supe- rieure. Deuxieme partie: Paleontologie. Les ammonites de la Craie superieure. Memoires du Service de la Carte Geologique Detaillee de la France, 1901: 264 p." type="book" year="1894">GROSSOUVRE, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FE26C7024076F9AC" author="DOUVILLE" box="[390,576,1633,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref8116" refString="DOUVILLE, H. (1916) - Les terrains secondaires dans le Massif du Moghara, a l'E de l'isthme de Suez. Memoires de l'Academie des Sciences de Paris (2), 54: 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1916">DOUVILLÉ, 1916</bibRefCitation>
, p. 120; pl. 15, fig. 7). 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FF45C7E14393F94C" author="MAHMOUD" box="[229,421,1665,1689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" refId="ref8835" refString="MAHMOUD, G. I. (1956) - Etudes paleontologiques sur la faune cretacique du Massif du Moghara (Sinai, Egypte). Publication de l'Institut du desert d'Egypte, 8: 192 p." type="book" year="1956">MAHMOUD (1956</bibRefCitation>
: p. 66) does not provide details about the locality or stratigraphic level of the specimen he figured, but MORET &amp; MAHMOUD (1953, p. 268 and 269) mentioned the species within their Levels 2 and 4, indicating an Early Albian age.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FF37C6404392F828" blockId="3.[151,757,696,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
The specimens figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FE0EC640400CF8EE" author="BASSE" box="[430,570,1827,1851]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="411 - 472" refId="ref7350" refString="BASSE, E. (1940) - Les Cephalopodes des massifs cotiers syriens. Notes et Memoires du Haut-Commissariat de la Republique Francaise en Syrie et au Liban, 3: Etudes paleontologiques, 411 - 472." type="book chapter" year="1940">BASSE (1940</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 4, fig. 1; textfigs 9, 10), from an unknown stratigraphic level of the Albian of Mdereidj, 
<collectingCountry id="45BE0EF4FFD1FF92FEDFC60043E9F8AE" box="[383,479,1891,1915]" name="Lebanon" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
, seem to be close to the present species by their general shape, suture and narrow concave ventral area, but the photographed specimen, herein figured (
<figureCitation id="A59252E1FFD1FF92FE9EC6A74348F808" box="[318,382,1988,2013]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[831,866,1030,1052]" captionTargetBox="[836,1436,257,978]" captionTargetId="figure-677@3.[836,1436,257,978]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3: Knemiceras sp. ind., the specimen figured by BASSE (1940, pl. 4, fig. 1; text fig. 9, 10), as Knemiceras gracile, from unknown stratigraphical level of the Albian of Mdereidj, Lebanon." pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) is too weathered and corroded to be specifically identified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FF37C9664192FA80" blockId="3.[151,757,696,2077]" lastBlockId="3.[831,1437,1212,1850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<materialsCitation id="8DC14439FFD1FF92FF37C9664197FA80" collectionCode="ARNOULD-" country="Tunisia" county="Tunisian" location="Early Albian" municipality="Furthermore" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
The specimens figured by 
<collectionCode id="5BB8D6A1FFD1FF92FE66C966400DF7C8" box="[454,571,2053,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">ARNOULD-</collectionCode>
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FD9BC96640E6F7C8" author="SAGET &amp; Contribution" box="[571,720,2053,2077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" refId="ref7316" refString="ARNOULD- SAGET, S. (1956) - Contribution a l'etude des Engo- noceratidae (les couches a Knemiceras du Sud-tunisien). Annales des Mines Geologiques, 20: 47 p." type="book" year="1956">SAGET (1956</bibRefCitation>
, p. 16, text-fig. 10; pl. 3, figs 3, 4), from the 
<location id="387618BFFFD1FF92FB57C5DF4749FB01" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:B500FF72FFD0FF92FC33C0624192F8EF:387618BFFFD1FF92FB57C5DF4749FB01" box="[1271,1407,1212,1236]" country="Tunisia" county="Tunisian" municipality="Furthermore" name="Early Albian" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Early Albian</location>
of southern 
<collectingCountry id="45BE0EF4FFD1FF92FC01C5BF41C5FB21" box="[929,1011,1244,1268]" name="Tunisia" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, are too weathered to be fully identified. 
<collectingMunicipality id="DD72D41EFFD1FF92FCE0C59F41FEFAC1" box="[832,968,1276,1300]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Furthermore</collectingMunicipality>
, the 
<collectingCounty id="D47736E8FFD1FF92FC5FC59F466DFAC1" box="[1023,1115,1276,1300]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Tunisian</collectingCounty>
specimens have a wider and flatter ventral area, and less convex flanks than the 
<typeStatus id="E212F0C6FFD1FF92FCE0C45E4197FA80" box="[832,929,1341,1365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">holotype</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FC9FC43D4625F96C" blockId="3.[831,1437,1212,1850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
ABU- 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FCD9C43D41CCFAA0" author="ZIED &amp; Biostratigraphic" box="[889,1018,1373,1397]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="125 - 158" refId="ref7241" refString="ABU- ZIED, R. H. (2006) - Biostratigraphic framework of some Lower Cretaceous outcrops from northern Sinai, Egypt based on cephalopods. Egyptian Journal of Paleontology, 6: 125 - 158." type="journal article" year="2006">ZIED (2006</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2r, pl. 6, figs 10-12; 2008, figs 2R, 7A-C) mistakely figured a single specimen from El Tourkumanyia, 
<collectingRegion id="FF6D8086FFD1FF92FBB4C4FD46A5FA63" box="[1044,1171,1438,1462]" country="Egypt" name="Shamal Sina'" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">north Sinai</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="45BE0EF4FFD1FF92FB05C4FC46D1FA62" box="[1189,1255,1439,1463]" name="Egypt" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FABDC4FC41BDFA03" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FABDC4FC41BDFA03" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The figured specimen, showing strong ribbing, wide umbilicus, pronounced umbilical tubercles, wide flat venter, and frilled suture. These morphological features seem to fall within the variability of 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FABDC7434673F98D" authority="MAHMOUD, 1956" authorityName="MAHMOUD" authorityYear="1956" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="spathi">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FABDC74341B6F98D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras spathi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FC28C7234673F98D" author="MAHMOUD" box="[904,1093,1600,1624]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" refId="ref8835" refString="MAHMOUD, G. I. (1956) - Etudes paleontologiques sur la faune cretacique du Massif du Moghara (Sinai, Egypte). Publication de l'Institut du desert d'Egypte, 8: 192 p." type="book" year="1956">MAHMOUD, 1956</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FB6AC72241C9F9AD" authority="DOUVILLE, 1916" authorityName="DOUVILLE" authorityYear="1916" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FB6AC72247ABF98D" box="[1226,1437,1600,1624]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras gracile</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FC9FC70241C9F9AD" author="DOUVILLE" box="[831,1023,1632,1657]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref8116" refString="DOUVILLE, H. (1916) - Les terrains secondaires dans le Massif du Moghara, a l'E de l'isthme de Suez. Memoires de l'Academie des Sciences de Paris (2), 54: 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1916">DOUVILLÉ, 1916</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the 
<taxonomicName id="FAA935E7FFD1FF92FB61C70247ABF9AD" box="[1217,1437,1632,1656]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Knemiceratidae" genus="Knemiceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FB61C70247ABF9AD" box="[1217,1437,1632,1656]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Knemiceras gracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
biozone of ABU- 
<bibRefCitation id="59383395FFD1FF92FC54C7E2464EF94C" author="ZIED &amp; Lithostratigraphy" box="[1012,1144,1665,1689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161" pagination="603 - 624" refId="ref7279" refString="ABU- ZIED, R. H. (2008) - Lithostratigraphy and biostratigraphy of some Lower Cretaceous outcrops from Northern Sinai, Egypt. Cretaceous Research, 29 (4): 603 - 624." type="journal article" year="2008">ZIED (2008)</bibRefCitation>
is not herein accepted and needs to be revised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D164E64FFD1FF92FC9FC7A24192F8EF" blockId="3.[831,1437,1212,1850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis id="0FDD9276FFD1FF92FC9FC7A241FBF90C" bold="true" box="[831,973,1729,1753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Occurrence:</emphasis>
Gabal Maaza, SE of the great Maghara Dome, 
<collectingRegion id="FF6D8086FFD1FF92FC34C7814627F92F" box="[916,1041,1762,1786]" country="Egypt" name="Shamal Sina'" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">north Sinai</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="45BE0EF4FFD1FF92FB82C7814652F92F" box="[1058,1124,1762,1786]" name="Egypt" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, Early Albian. This species is doubtfully reported from the Albian of Mderedj, 
<collectingCountry id="45BE0EF4FFD1FF92FC9FC6414196F8EF" box="[831,928,1826,1850]" name="Lebanon" pageId="3" pageNumber="161">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
